timelogger.sh - timelogging made easy

timelogger logs your time to a local git repo and pushes it to a remote.
to get started simply type
    bash timelogger.sh --init

to log your time type
    bash timelogger.sh --project myproject --hours 8 --message "worked on project"

usage: timelogger.sh
-u | --user       Your username
-r | --remote     Timelogging repository
-b | --branch     Userbranch
-d | --date       Date of worklog
-p | --project    Project you worked on
-h | --hours      How many hours you worked
-m | --message    The description of the worklog
     --init            Initialize / reset your timelogger
     --help            Print this help

